  "original_title": "\u0db1\u0ddc\u0d9c\u0dd0\u0dc5\u0db4\u0dd9\u0db1 \u0daf\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba \u0db8\u0dd0\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd2 103\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "103 unfit train carriages were brought",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Parliamentary Committee on Government Accounts (COPA) has expressed its displeasure regarding the huge waste of money caused by the importation of 103 railway carriages from India which cannot be used in this country.",
        "It is revealed in COPA committee that out of 160 railway carriages brought from India, 103 have not been put to use so far.",
        "In an inquiry made by the said committee, the head of the railway department said that the vacuum brake system exists in the railway carriages in this country, but the air brake system exists in these new railway carriages.",
        "The members asked who approved the importation of these train carriages which are not suitable for the country. They further mentioned that the officials who took that decision should be held responsible for this.",
        "The information about this was revealed when the Committee on Government Accounts met last (05th) under the chairmanship of its Chairman, Member of Parliament Professor Tissa Witharana."
      ],
